AB Most sociology departments provide students with the opportunity to
   participate in an internship. Yet faculty members often remain skeptical
   about the academic rigor of such experience-based learning. This paper
   argues that internships help students achieve the educational goals of
   most sociology programs. internships provide students with an extended
   opportunity to apply the sociological perspective to a "real world"
