   chronic conditions, adverse lifestyle practices, outpatient and
   emergency department use and hospitalization rates, and use of
   preventive screening measures. Both homeless mothers and housed mothers
   demonstrated low levels of physical and role functioning and high levels
   of bodily pain. Prevalence rates of asthma, anemia, and ulcer disease
   were high in both groups. More than half of both groups were current
