   lower health status, more chronic health problems, and higher smoking
   rates than the general population. High rates of hospitalization,
   emergency department visits, and more risk behaviors among homeless
   mothers suggest that they are at even greater risk of adverse health
   outcomes. Efforts to address gaps in access to primary care and to
   integrate psychosocial supports with health care delivery may improve
   health outcomes for homeless mothers and reduce use of costly medical
   care services.
