   modeling of transmission could play an crucial role in showing us both
   the geography of human rights and social inequalities, and demonstrating
   how processes such as climate change interact with human rights to favor
   disease emergence. Spatial analyses can also indicate where structural
   and environmental interventions to promote human behavior change might
