   male and female adolescents reporting being forced or pressured to have
   sex. Having been forced or pressured to have sex was associated with
   externalizing behavior, such as fighting, among girls and with
   internalizing behavior, such as bulimia, among boys. These unexpected
   associations have notable implications for screening adolescents for a
   history of having been forced or pressured to have sex.
