   channelization. On the one hand, once an area or region takes a given
   developmental direction, both the process of specialization in a given
   primary activity and the investment of human and economic capital in the
   capture of linkages tied to that primary activity can set in motion a
   process that may effectively preclude other developmental options. On
   the other hand, a given course of development can also be pursued so
   intensively as to bring about its demise.
