   positive developments and problems experienced by departments and the
   discipline in general. Issues examined include student enrollment and
   degree recipients over the last two decades, enrollment trends in other
   disciplines, recent trends in advertised sociology faculty positions,
   the status of women and minorities, and which departments have and have
   not been eliminated. Based upon this assessment and the growing
   literature in the field dealing with these issues, future prospects for
   departments are discussed, problem areas are identified, and
   recommendations are made concerning the strengthening of the profession.
